# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the case-scheduler Next.js project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Package**: `@vercel/speed-insights` v2.0.0
- **Method**: Installed via npm as specified by the project's package manager
- **Files Modified**:
  - `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights to dependencies
  - `package-lock.json` - Updated lockfile with new dependency tree

### 2. Speed Insights Integration
- **File Modified**: `src/app/layout.tsx`
- **Changes**:
  - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag

## Implementation Details

This project uses **Next.js 15.2.3 with the App Router**, so I followed the official Vercel documentation for Next.js 13.5+ applications:

1. Fetched the latest installation instructions from: https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart
2. Installed the `@vercel/speed-insights` package using npm
3. Added the SpeedInsights component to the root layout file (`src/app/layout.tsx`)
4. Placed the component inside the `<body>` tag after existing content, following Next.js best practices

The SpeedInsights component is now globally available across all pages of the application.

## Code Structure
The implementation preserves the existing code structure:
- Maintained all existing imports and their order
- Placed SpeedInsights component at the end of the body section
- No changes to existing functionality or components
- Follows the project's TypeScript and formatting conventions

## Verification

✅ **TypeScript Compilation**: Passed - no type errors
✅ **Code Formatting**: Passed - layout.tsx follows Prettier conventions
✅ **Package Installation**: Successful - @vercel/speed-insights@2.0.0 installed
✅ **Lockfile Updated**: package-lock.json properly updated

## Notes

- The Speed Insights component will automatically collect Web Vitals data when the application is deployed to Vercel
- No additional configuration is required for basic functionality
- The component is lightweight and will not impact page load performance
- To view metrics, enable Speed Insights in the Vercel project dashboard after deployment

## Next Steps

To see Speed Insights data:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard for this project
3. Visit the deployed site to generate traffic
4. View real-time performance metrics in the Speed Insights dashboard

The installation is complete and ready for deployment.
